[The virus is closely related to rabies virus, so it is sensible to be treated with a rabies vaccine. There have been some reports in diverse media of microbats being in the area, but they have not been verified.

Microbats does not necessarily mean small, as they often range in size from 4-16 cm (1.6-6.3 in) in length. They may be insect or fruit bats, and vampire bats are often in this category. Likely, the biosecurity folks have some sort of provision for observation of bats in the area.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Australia can be accessed at http://healthmap.org/r/1kJr. - Mod.TG]

[There are no blood-sucking bats in Australia -- their range is confined to Mexico & South America. The location of Highborne Farm is given as north of Warwick, which is
SW of Brisbane -- see map:
<www.hotelsaccommodation.com.au/images/small-maps/Warwick-Queensland.gif>
- Mod.JW]
